\hypertarget{about}{%
\subsection{About}\label{about}}

This script is an exploration of using a random forest to train and
classify satisfaction ratings of airline passengers.

Data source:
\url{https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/teejmahal20/airline-passenger-satisfaction}

\hypertarget{clean-data}{%
\subsubsection{Clean data}\label{clean-data}}

Remove any rows with NA (for simplicty) \#remove na values (any row with
na)

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\NormalTok{training\_df }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{na.omit}\NormalTok{(training\_df)}
\NormalTok{test\_df }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{na.omit}\NormalTok{(test\_df)}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

Ensure satisfaction is a factor

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\NormalTok{training\_df}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{satisfaction }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{as.factor}\NormalTok{(training\_df}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{satisfaction)}
\NormalTok{test\_df}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{satisfaction }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{as.factor}\NormalTok{(test\_df}\SpecialCharTok{$}\NormalTok{satisfaction)}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}

Create Random Forest

\begin{Shaded}
\begin{Highlighting}[]
\NormalTok{rf }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \FunctionTok{randomForest}\NormalTok{(satisfaction }\SpecialCharTok{\textasciitilde{}}\NormalTok{., }\AttributeTok{data=}\NormalTok{training\_df[}\DecValTok{1}\SpecialCharTok{:}\DecValTok{200}\NormalTok{,])}
\NormalTok{rf}
\end{Highlighting}
\end{Shaded}
